==English==
===Transitive verb phrase===
'''to [[chat]] up''' ('''chats up''', '''chatting up''', '''chatted up''')

#To talk to (someone) [[flirtatious]]ly with the intention of establishing a [[romantic]] or [[sexual]] [[encounter]] or [[relationship]] with that person.

====Usage notes====
*The subject of '''chat up''' is inserted between the components of this phrase:
*:''to chat someone up''